    <h1 id="myHeader">Chocolate-Mint Chocolate Cookies</h1>
  <p>Melted créme de menthe candies placed on top of small chocolate cookies.
  A delight for those who love mint and chocolate and perfect for gatherings!</p>
  <!-- Multiple similar elements -->
    <h2 class="Information">Servings</h2>
  <p>Makes 2 - 1/2 Dozen (depending on size of dough).</p>
    <h3 class="Information">Bake time</h3>
  <p>8-10 minuites.</p>
    <h3 class="Information">Temperature</h3>
  <p>350°F</p>
    <h3 class="Information">Ingredients</h3>
<!-- Site navigation menu -->
<ul class="navbar">
  <li>Semisweet chocolate chips: 1 cup (6 oz.)</li>
  <li>Butter: 6 tablespoons</li>
  <li>Light brown sugar: 3/4 cup</li>
  <li>Water: 1 tablespoon</li>
  <li>Egg(s): 1, large</li>
  <li>All-purpose Flour: 1-1/4 cup</li>
  <li>Salt: 1/2 teaspoon</li>
  <li>Baking Soda: 1/2 teaspoon</li>
  <li>Créme de menthe chocolate candies: 1 (4.67 oz.) package</li>
</ul>

<!-- Main content -->
<div class='content'>
  <h2 class="Information">Directions</h2>
    <p>In a small saucepan over medium heat, melt chocolatre chips and butter.
    In a large bowl with an electric mixer on medium-low speed, combine the
    melted chocolate mixture, brown sugar, and water; let cool slightly. Slowly
    beat in an egg. Gradually add flour, salt, and baking soda untill well combined.
    Cover and put the mixture into the refrigorator. Let the mixture chill for 1 hour.</p>

    <p>Pre-heat oven to 350 degrees F. Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches
      apart on greased cookie sheets.</p>

    <p>Bake 10-8 minuites or untill the edges are set and the middles are soft and slightly
       puffy. Remove from oven and palce on a cooling rack.</p>

    <p>Cut 15 candies in half and place them a half on top of each warm cookie; let sit for
      1 minute. Gently spread warmed chocolate over tops of cookies and let cool slightly.
      Chop remaining candies and sprinkle on top of cookies, as shown in the photo.</p>
</div>
</body>
